---
import SiteLayout from '../../layouts/SiteLayout.astro';
import BilibiliPlayer from '../../components/BilibiliPlayer.astro';
---

<SiteLayout
  title="Sunken City Case Study — Jadey"
  description="A portfolio case study covering underwater gameplay, systemic interaction, puzzles, and level design in Unreal Engine 5."
>
  <article class="case-study">
    <header class="case-hero section-pad">
      <a class="back-link" href="/design/#work">← Design projects</a>
      <div class="case-title-row">
        <div data-reveal>
          <p class="eyebrow">Gameplay systems · Level design</p>
          <h1>Sunken City</h1>
          <p class="case-deck">
            An underwater exploration prototype where traversal, oxygen pressure, interaction, and
            environmental puzzles share one readable design language.
          </p>
        </div>
        <dl class="case-facts" data-reveal>
          <div><dt>Role</dt><dd>Gameplay Programmer<br />Level Designer</dd></div>
          <div><dt>Engine</dt><dd>Unreal Engine 5.4.4</dd></div>
          <div><dt>Platform</dt><dd>Windows PC</dd></div>
          <div><dt>Status</dt><dd>Portfolio prototype</dd></div>
        </dl>
      </div>
      <div class="case-hero-art ocean-visual" data-reveal>
        <div class="visual-grid"></div>
        <svg viewBox="0 0 1200 580" aria-hidden="true">
          <path d="M40 420c143-148 260-248 425-216 130 25 170 122 284 61 164-87 250 15 414 163" />
          <path d="M18 505c180-113 314-70 417-167 114-108 214 13 308 24 158 18 264 50 447 147" />
          <circle cx="454" cy="267" r="58" />
          <circle cx="832" cy="340" r="34" />
        </svg>
        <div class="case-art-copy">
          <span>CASE STUDY / 01</span>
          <strong>DESCEND.<br />READ.<br />SOLVE.</strong>
        </div>
      </div>
    </header>

    <section class="case-section section-pad" aria-labelledby="overview-title">
      <div class="case-sidebar">
        <p class="section-index">01 / OVERVIEW</p>
      </div>
      <div class="case-content" data-reveal>
        <h2 id="overview-title">The design challenge</h2>
        <p class="lead-copy">
          Make underwater traversal feel unfamiliar without becoming unreadable, then teach the player
          enough of its rules to solve physical puzzles under light resource pressure.
        </p>
        <div class="goal-grid">
          <div><span>01</span><h3>Readable movement</h3><p>Use space and landmarks to teach dive, ascend, and acceleration.</p></div>
          <div><span>02</span><h3>Systemic puzzles</h3><p>Reuse carrying, throwing, pressure, and weight instead of one-off interactions.</p></div>
          <div><span>03</span><h3>Controlled pressure</h3><p>Let oxygen shape pacing while keeping exploration approachable.</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="case-section section-pad case-section-dark" aria-labelledby="video-title">
      <div class="case-sidebar"><p class="section-index">02 / IN MOTION</p></div>
      <div class="case-content" data-reveal>
        <div class="inline-heading">
          <h2 id="video-title">Video belongs beside the decision.</h2>
          <p>This uses the same reusable Bilibili component as the homepage.</p>
        </div>
        <BilibiliPlayer bvid="BV1mfTW6vESe" title="Bilibili embed demo inside a portfolio case study" />
        <p class="media-credit">Demo reference video — the finished case study will use your own gameplay reel.</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="case-section section-pad" aria-labelledby="flow-title">
      <div class="case-sidebar"><p class="section-index">03 / LEVEL FLOW</p></div>
      <div class="case-content" data-reveal>
        <h2 id="flow-title">Teach → test → remix</h2>
        <p class="lead-copy">
          The level introduces one verb in safety, tests it with a clear objective, then combines it with
          oxygen pressure and object interaction.
        </p>
        <div class="flow-diagram" aria-label="Four-stage level flow">
          <div><span>01</span><strong>Safe descent</strong><small>Learn vertical movement</small></div>
          <i aria-hidden="true">→</i>
          <div><span>02</span><strong>Visible goal</strong><small>Read the locked route</small></div>
          <i aria-hidden="true">→</i>
          <div><span>03</span><strong>Pressure test</strong><small>Carry under oxygen cost</small></div>
          <i aria-hidden="true">→</i>
          <div><span>04</span><strong>Remix</strong><small>Combine learned rules</small></div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="case-section section-pad" aria-labelledby="iteration-title">
      <div class="case-sidebar"><p class="section-index">04 / ITERATION</p></div>
      <div class="case-content" data-reveal>
        <h2 id="iteration-title">Make the change visible.</h2>
        <p class="lead-copy">A final case study should show evidence of what changed and why. These frames demonstrate the intended presentation.</p>
        <div class="iteration-grid">
          <figure class="iteration-frame iteration-before">
            <div class="blockout-scene"><i></i><i></i><i></i><i></i></div>
            <figcaption><span>Before / V01</span><strong>Goal and route competed for attention</strong></figcaption>
          </figure>
          <figure class="iteration-frame iteration-after">
            <div class="blockout-scene"><i></i><i></i><i></i><i></i></div>
            <figcaption><span>After / V03</span><strong>Landmark, light, and framing align</strong></figcaption>
          </figure>
        </div>
        <aside class="decision-callout">
          <span>Design decision</span>
          <p>Move the objective above the horizon line, reduce competing silhouettes, and make the return path reuse the same landmark from a new angle.</p>
        </aside>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="next-case section-pad" data-reveal>
      <p class="section-index">NEXT</p>
      <a href="/analysis/player-guidance/">
        <span>Read the related design note</span>
        <strong>Teaching movement through space <i>↗</i></strong>
      </a>
    </section>
  </article>
</SiteLayout>
